  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add Thai chili peppers to the pan and sauté for another minute.",
    "Add hoisin sauce, fish sauce, lime juice, garlic, and ginger to the pan and stir to combine.",
    "Add coconut milk to the pan and bring to a simmer.",
    "Reduce heat to low and let simmer for 5 minutes.",
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Cut bread into small cubes and toast in the oven until crispy, about 5 minutes.",
    "Finely chop peanuts and set aside.",
    "To assemble the salad, place a portion of the chicken mixture onto a corn husk, followed by crispy bread, chopped peanuts, and fresh cilantro.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!",
    "Refrigerate leftovers for up to 3 days.",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving."
